# Commit message template for conventional commits
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Type (required): feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, chore
# Scope (optional): trees, graphs, lists, skiplist, etc.
# Subject (required): short description
#
# Examples:
#   feat(trees): add AVL tree implementation
#   fix(graphs): correct Dijkstra algorithm edge case
#   docs: update installation instructions in README
#   test(lists): add comprehensive linked list tests
#   refactor(skiplist): improve search performance
#
# Breaking changes:
#   feat!: redesign Graph API
#   OR
#   feat: change API structure
#   
#   BREAKING CHANGE: Graph now uses node IDs instead of labels
#
# Version bumps:
#   fix:     → PATCH (0.0.X) - bug fixes
#   feat:    → MINOR (0.X.0) - new features
#   feat!:   → MAJOR (X.0.0) - breaking changes
#   BREAKING CHANGE: → MAJOR (X.0.0)
#
# Body (optional): Explain what and why (not how)
# Footer (optional): Reference issues, breaking changes
